post.description:
Search the library for tracks where ``query`` contains attributes ``uri``, ``track_name``, ``album``, ``artist``,
``albumartist``, ``composer``, ``performer``, ``track_no``, ``genre``,
``date``, ``comment`` or ``any``. Any of the query attributes is an array of strings, where the string items are the strings for which that attributes is matched against in the backend. 

If ``uris`` is given, the search is limited to results from within the
URI roots. For example passing ``{"uris": ["file:"]}`` will limit the search
to the local backend.

### Attributes
- `query` – one or more queries to search for  
- `uris` (list of string or None) – zero or more URI roots to limit the search to  
- `exact` (bool) – if the search should use exact matching

### Examples

- Returns results matching 'a' in any backend:  
```json
{
  "query": {
    "any": ["a"]
  }
}
```

- Returns results matching artist 'xyz' in any backend:  
```json
{
  "query": {
    "artist": ["xyz"]
  }
}
```

- Returns results matching 'a' and 'b' and artist 'xyz' in any backend:  
```json
{
  "query": {
    "any": ["a", "b"],
    "artist": ["xyz"]
  }
}
```

- Returns results matching 'a' if within the given URI roots
"file:///media/music" and "spotify:":  

```json
{
  "query": {
    "any": ["a"]
  },
  "uris": ["file:///media/music", "spotify:"]
}
```

- Returns results matching artist 'xyz' and 'abc' in any backend:  
```json
{
  "query": {
    "artist": ["xyz", "abc"]
  }
}
```

## Success
A successful request has returns an array of serach results, with status code `201`. Every item in the array is a json representation of a [mopidy data model](https://docs.mopidy.com/en/latest/api/models/#module-mopidy.models), e.g. `Track`, `Artist`, `Album` etc.

## Errors
For client errors the response status code is `400`, and the body contains an error message. For example a malformed search request.

For errors in the backend the response status code is `500`, and the body contains an error message.
